policy.%20It's%20deducted%20automatically%20from%20my%20husband's%20paycheck%2C%20since%20he%20gets%20a%20discount%20through%20work.%20(Worth%20noting%2C%20the%20premium%20is%20much%20higher%20than%20it%20was%20when%20he%20was%20a%20pup.%20Just%20like%20humans%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20insurance%20goes%20up%20as%20you%20age.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20policy%20is%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fnationwide-pet-insurance-review%5C%22%3ENationwide%20Pet%20Insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20(yep%2C%20they%20have%20pet%20insurance%2C%20too!)%20and%20offers%2070%25%20reimbursement%20after%20we%20reach%20our%20%24250%20deductible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20covers%20accidents%20such%20as%20broken%20bones%2C%20sprains%2C%20and%20ingested%20items%3B%20illnesses%20such%20as%20ear%20infections%2C%20vomiting%2C%20cancer%2C%20and%20diabetes%3B%20and%20wellness%20checkups%20and%20vaccinations%2C%20bloodwork%2C%20and%20heartworm%20and%20flea%20control.%20The%20annual%20maximum%20benefit%20is%20%247%2C500%2C%20so%20that's%20worth%20keeping%20in%20mind%20when%20faced%20with%20a%20major%20health%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFor%20an%20older%20dog%2C%20medical%20conditions%20could%20cost%20thousands%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20always%20tell%20everyone%20my%20first%20baby%20wasn't%20a%20human.%20Rather%2C%20he%20came%20in%20the%20form%20of%20one%20very%20needy%2C%20adorable%20French%20bulldog.%20These%20days%2C%20he's%20considered%20a%20dog%20senior%20citizen.%20And%20while%20we've%20contemplated%20canceling%20his%20policy%20more%20than%20once%2C%20I'm%20so%20glad%20we%20didn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20my%20dog%20has%20been%20relatively%20healthy%20throughout%20his%20life%2C%20he's%20had%20a%20few%20medical%20conditions%20that%20we've%20had%20to%20deal%20with%2C%20such%20as%20some%20periodontal%20disease%20to%20recurring%20tail%20infections.%20These%20issues%20would%20have%20cost%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20care%2C%20respectively%2C%20had%20we%20not%20had%20pet%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20try%20to%20see%20a%20vet%20twice%20a%20year%3B%20French%20bulldogs%20are%20more%20likely%20than%20other%20breeds%20to%20deal%20with%20heatstroke%2C%20sensitive%20skin%2C%20ear%20infractions%2C%20and%20breathing%20issues%2C%20just%20to%20name%20a%20few.%20So%20it%20makes%20sense%2C%20both%20financially%20and%20from%20a%20health%20perspective%2C%20to%20stay%20on%20top%20of%20their%20veterinary%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20pugs%2C%20English%20bulldogs%2C%20and%20Boston%20terriers%2C%20French%20bulldogs%20are%20brachycephalic%20dogs.%20This%20means%20their%20snouts%20are%20shorter%20than%20other%20dogs'%2C%20and%20they%20can%20have%20smaller%20nostrils%20and%20windpipes%2C%20which%20can%20translate%20into%20breathing%20issues%20or%20brachycephalic%20obstructive%20airway%20syndrome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20breeds%20are%20also%20more%20likely%20to%20deal%20with%20heat%20intolerance%2C%20skin%20issues%2C%20dental%20disease%2C%20and%20pneumonia.%20That's%20another%20reason%20we've%20always%20had%20pet%20insurance%20for%20our%20dog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20much%20we've%20saved%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20little%20guy%20has%20been%20hospitalized%20once%20in%20his%20life%20for%20pancreatitis%20after%20eating%20one%20too%20many%20rogue%20meatballs%20our%20two-year-old%20dropped.%20He's%20also%20had%20recurring%20tail%20infections%2C%20many%20gastrointestinal%20issues%2C%20and%20now%20his%20liver%20issue.%20Each%20instance%20would%20have%20cost%20us%20thousands%3B%20instead%2C%20we've%20paid%20the%20%24250%20deductible%20and%20the%20remaining%2030%25%20of%20the%20vet%20bill%2C%20which%20cut%20our%20costs%20dramatically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20we've%20shopped%20around%20over%20the%20course%20of%20his%20life%2C%20too.%20His%20first%20policy%20was%20through%20PetPlan%2C%20now%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffetch-pet-insurance-review%5C%22%3EFetch%20Pet%20Insurance%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Fetch%20cover