0Go%20Online%20Amid%2047%20Degrees%20In%20This%20Country%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EExtreme%20heat%20scorched%20the%20Philippines%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20forcing%20thousands%20of%20schools%20to%20suspend%20in-person%20classes%20and%20prompting%20warnings%20for%20people%20to%20limit%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20spent%20outdoors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20months%20of%20March%2C%20April%20and%20May%20are%20typically%20the%20hottest%20and%20driest%20in%20the%20archipelago%20nation%2C%20but%20conditions%20this%20year%20have%20been%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20El%20Nino%20weather%20phenomenon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20so%20hot%20you%20can't%20breathe%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Erlin%20Tumaron%2C%2060%2C%20who%20works%20at%20a%20seaside%20resort%20in%20Cavite%20province%2C%20south%20of%20Manila%2C%20where%20the%20heat%20index%20reached%2047%20degrees%20Celsius%20(117%20degrees%20Fahrenheit)%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20surprising%20our%20pools%20are%20still%20empty.%20You%20would%20expect%20people%20to%20come%20and%20take%20a%20swim%2C%20but%20it%20seems%20they're%20reluctant%20to%20leave%20their%20homes%20because%20of%20the%20heat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20heat%20index%20was%20expected%20to%20reach%20the%20%26quot%3Bdanger%26quot%3B%20level%20of%2042C%20or%20higher%20in%20at%20least%2030%20cities%20and%20municipalities%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20state%20weather%20forecaster%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20heat%20index%20measures%20what%20a%20temperature%20feels%20like%2C%20taking%20into%20account%20humidity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Education%2C%20which%20oversees%20more%20than%2047%2C600%20schools%2C%20said%20nearly%206%2C700%20schools%20suspended%20in-person%20classes%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%2050%20percent%20chance%20of%20the%20heat%20intensifying%20in%20the%20coming%20days%2C%20said%20Ana%20Solis%2C%20chief%20climatologist%20at%20the%20state%20weather%20forecaster.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20limit%20the%20time%20we%20spend%20outdoors%2C%20drink%20plenty%20of%20water%2C%20bring%20umbrellas%20and%20hats%20when%20going%20outdoors%2C%26quot%3B%20Solis%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESolis%20said%20El%20Nino%20was%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Bextreme%20heat%26quot%3B%20affecting%20swaths%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%20half%20the%20country's%20provinces%20are%20officially%20in%20drought.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'It's%20really%20hot%20here'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20northern%20municipality%20of%20Aparri%20endured%20a%20heat%20index%20of%2048C%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20highest%20in%20the%20country%2C%20and%20was%20expected%20to%20hit%2045C%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20actual%20maximum%20air%20temperature%20was%2036.4C%20(97.5F)%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20with%2035C%20forecast%20for%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20hot%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Eric%20Vista%20of%20the%20municipal%20disaster%20agency%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVista%20said%20a%20shower%20of%20rain%20on%20Tuesday%20night%20offered%20some%20temporary%20relief%20but%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bback%20to%20being%20super%20hot%26quot%3B%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESweltering%20temperatures%20in%20the%20capital%20Manila%20forced%20more%20than%20400%20schools%20to%20switch%20to%20remote%20learning.%20The%20heat%20index%20reached%2045C%20on%20Tuesday%20and%20was%20expected%20to%20hit%2044C%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETuesday's%20actual%20high%20in%20the%20city%20was%2037.1C.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20drought-stricken%20Occidental%20Mindoro%20province%2C%20government%20employee%20Mary%20Ann%20Gener%20said%20people%20working%20indoors%20where%20there%20was%20air%20conditioning%20were%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20terrible%20for%20those%20outside%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20get%20a%20headache%20immediately%20after%20you%20go%20out.%20You%20really%20need%20to%20hydrate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Dagupan%20city%2C%20north%20of%20Manila%2C%20university%20employee%20Edz%20Alteros%20said%20she%20and%20her%20colleagues%20no%20longer%20went%20out%20for%20lunch%20because%20of%20the%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20heat%20index%20there%20reached%2047C%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20get%20somebody%20to%20buy%20food%20and%20we%20eat%20inside%20the%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20Alteros%2C%2027%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20air%20conditioning%20is%20set%20at%2014-18C%20during%20the%20hottest%20part%20of%20the%20day%2C%20but%20we%20ease%20up%20at%20other%20times%20to%20prevent%20the%20aircon%20from%20breaking%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlobal%20temperatures%20hit%20record%20highs%20last%20year%2C%20and%20the%20United%20Nation's%20weather%20and%20climate%20agency%20said%20Tuesday%20that%20Asia%20was%20warming%20at%20a%20particularly%20rapid%20pace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Philippines%20ranks%20among%20the%20countries%20most%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713957900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fmjlcta88_philippines-generic_625x300_24_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fits-really-hot-here-schools-go-online-amid-extreme-heat-in-philippines-5512918%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Extreme%20heat%20scorched%20the%20Philippines%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20forcing%20thousands%20of%20schools%20to%20suspend%20in-person%20classes%20and%20prompting%20warnings%20for%20people%20to%20limit%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20spent%20outdoors.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworl