%80%94%20we%20know%20because%20we%20have%20five%20kids%20between%20us%20(three%20for%20Kristin%20and%20two%20for%20Deena).%20But%20what's%20even%20more%20challenging%20than%20parenting%20is%20raising%20ourselves%20in%20the%20process.%20Because%20amid%20all%20those%20sleepless%20infant%20nights%20and%20toddler%20meltdowns%2C%20we're%20growing%20and%20changing%20ourselves.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHow%20do%20we%20balance%20all%20that%3F%20With%20these%20seven%20steps.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3ENormalize%20tantrums%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20what%20your%20judge%20mother-in-law%20or%20store%20clerk%20might%20lead%20you%20to%20think%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexperienced-nanny-shares-her-techniques-for-dealing-with-tantrums-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etoddler%20tantrums%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20are%20entirely%20normal.%20In%20fact%2C%20they're%20actually%20a%20sign%20of%20healthy%20brain%20development.%20Next%20time%20your%20kid%20is%20having%20a%20meltdown%2C%20remember%20that%20you're%20not%20doing%20anything%20wrong%20and%20you%20absolutely%20do%20not%20have%20a%20bad%20kid.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3EPlay%20the%20long%20game%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere's%20no%20way%20to%20stop%20every%20tantrum%2C%20but%20you%20can%20prevent%20some%20of%20them.%20The%20way%20we%20respond%20can%20either%20level%20tantrums%20up%20or%20dial%20them%20down%2C%20and%20our%20response%20has%20an%20impact%20on%20the%20length%2C%20strength%2C%20and%20number%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-6-year-old-only-has-tantrums-around-his-grandparents-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etantrums%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20future.%20You%20don't%20have%20to%20get%20it%20right%20every%20time%2C%20but%20taking%20steps%20to%20rethink%20how%20you%20respond%20to%20tantrums%20can%20help%20throughout%20the%20toddler%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3EDon't%20escalate%2C%20don't%20negotiate%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20we%20escalate%20alongside%20our%20toddlers%20or%20try%20to%20negotiate%20with%20them%2C%20we're%20only%20going%20to%20make%20a%20tantrum%20bigger.%20It's%20like%20adding%20fuel%20to%20the%20fire.%20Instead%2C%20channel%20your%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmindfulness-meditation-how-to-do-it-2017-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einner%20calm%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20best%20you%20can.%20Let%20that%20calm%20be%20contagious.%20You'll%20see%20the%20tantrum%20start%20to%20dial%20down.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYes%2C%20we%20know%20this%20is%20extremely%20hard.%20You%20won't%20get%20it%20right%20every%20time%2C%20and%20that's%20OK.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3EValidate%20the%20feeling%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt's%20so%20tempting%20to%20try%20to%20fix%20our%20toddler's%20feelings%2C%20but%20doing%20that%20can%20accidentally%20diminish%20them.%20Avoid%20saying%20things%20that%20diminish%20their%20feelings%2C%20like%20%26quot%3BStop%20crying.%20You're%20fine!%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20a%20crayon!%20We%20have%20a%20million%20crayons.%20Calm%20down!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInstead%2C%20let%20your%20kid%20be%20heard%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20about%20a%20purple%20crayon%20being%2C%20well%2C%20purple-y.%20Making%20them%20feel%20seen%20and%20heard%20can%20shorten%20a%20tantrum%20and%20even%20stop%20a%20tantrum%20in%20its%20tracks.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3EHold%20the%20boundary%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20biggest%20hack%20for%20preventing%20tantrums%20is%20simply%20holding%20a%20boundary%20over%20and%20over%20and%20over%20again.%20Over%20time%2C%20your%20toddler%20learns%20that%20when%20you%20say%20%26quot%3Bone%20more%20episode%2C%26quot%3B%20that%20means%20one%20more%20episode%20%E2%80%94%20and%20no%20amount%20of%20tantruming%2C%20crying%2C%20or%20pushback%20will%20change%20that.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20may%20seem%20harsh%2C%20but%20it's%20really%20kind%20and%20loving.%20Your%20kid%20might%20seem%20like%20they%20want%20to%20make%20all%20the%20decisions%2C%20but%20really%2C%20they%20feel%20safest%20when%20you're%20the%20confident%20leader%20of%20your%20home%20with%20clear%2C%20consistent%20boundaries.%20Sticking%20to%20those%20is%20critical%20for%20preventing%20tantrums.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3EShift%20to%20the%20yes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToddlers%20hear%20%26quot%3Bno%26quot%3B%20all%20daylong.%20So%2C%20try%20to%20tell%20them%20yes.%20For%20example%2C%20when%20you're%20saying%20no%20more%20screen%20time%2C%20offer%20them%20an%20alternative%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20snack%20time.%20Would%20you%20like%20your%20red%20or%20blue%20cup%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20you%20shift%20to%20the%20yes%2C%20you're%20taking%20the%20focus%20away%20from%20the%20%26quot%3Bno%26quot%3B%20element%20of%20the%20boundary%2C%20and%20instead%2C%20you're%20giving%20your%20tot%20a%20little%20piece%20of%20age-appropriate%20power.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3ETake%20care%20of%20yourself%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe've%20both%20needed%20to%20take%20intentional%20steps%20to%20work%20on%20ourselves%20as%20parents.%20Sometimes%2C%20that%20can%20happen%20at%20home%2C%20like%20when%20Deana%20went%20through%20a%20conscious%20and%20intentional%20restructuring%20of%20her%20communication%20patterns%20with%20her%20husband.%20Sometimes%2C%20you%20need%20professional%20guidance.%20Therapy%20has%20literally%20been%20lifesaving%20for%20Kristin%2C%20allowing%20her%20to%20manage%20anxiety%20as%20a%20mom.%20We%20want%20to%20raise%20emotionally%20resilient%20kids%2C%20and%20that%20means%20building%20