o%20shifting%20from%20coastal%20cities%20in%20the%20Northeast%20and%20West%20to%20the%20Southeast%20US%20and%20Mountain%20West%2C%26quot%3B%20Gusto%20economist%20Luke%20Pardue%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgusto.com%2Fcompany-news%2Fsouthern-and-western-cities-lead-entrepreneurship-in-2022%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJuly%202023%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20might%20be%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20shift%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-economy-us-south-texas-florida-houston-dallas-nashville-miami-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecenter%20of%20the%20US%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpopulation-boom-south-texas-georgia-dallas-houston-atlanta-movers-homebuyers-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecountry's%20population%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20moves%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20young%20people%20have%20entered%20the%20ranks%20of%20entrepreneurs%20in%20recent%20years.%20Among%20US%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eadults%20between%2018%20and%2034%20years%20old%2C%2027%25%20were%20actively%20engaged%20in%20starting%20or%20running%20a%20new%20business%2C%20per%20the%20Babson%20report%2C%20That%20was%20nearly%20twice%20as%20high%20as%20the%2035-to-64%20age%20group%2C%20at%2014.5%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Kauffman%20Foundation%20report%20found%20rising%20entrepreneurship%20rates%20among%20older%20workers.%20In%202021%2C%20nearly%2023%25%20of%20new%20entrepreneurs%20were%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2055%20and%2064%2C%20up%20from%20about%2015%25%20in%201996.%20Still%2C%20the%20largest%20share%20of%20new%20entrepreneurs%2C%20about%2026%25%2C%20came%20from%20the%2020%20to%2034-year-old%20age%20cohort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEntrepreneurs%20are%20also%20clustered%20in%20certain%20industries%3A%20In%202022%2C%20the%20most%20common%20industry%20for%20new%20entrepreneurs%20was%20wholesale%2C%20retail%2C%20and%20hospitality%2C%20which%20accounted%20for%20about%2028%25%20of%20new%20business%20formations%2C%20per%20the%20Babson%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20Americans%20want%20to%20be%20entrepreneurs%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20it's%20going%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20more%20work-life%20flexibility%2C%20becoming%20financially%20stable%2C%20and%20supplementing%20income%20were%20the%20top%20motivations%20new%20entrepreneurs%20gave%20for%20starting%20their%20businesses%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Gusto%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20half%20of%20new%20entrepreneurs%20said%20they%20relied%20on%20personal%20savings%20to%20start%20their%20businesses.%20Eight%20percent%20took%20out%20a%20private%20business%20loan%2C%207%25%20got%20a%20loan%20from%20family%20or%20friends%2C%20and%203%25%20got%20a%20Small%20Business%20Administration-backed%20loan.%20Thirty-one%20percent%20said%20no%20funding%20was%20needed%20to%20start%20their%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFifty-six%20percent%20of%20new%20entrepreneurs%20said%20they%20didn't%20have%20another%20job%20when%20they%20started%20their%20business%2C%20compared%20to%2025%25%20who%20had%20a%20full-time%20job%20and%2019%25%20who%20had%20a%20part-time%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20they%20get%20their%20businesses%20up%20and%20running%2C%20self-employed%20workers%20feel%20pretty%20good%20about%20their%20gigs%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-read%2F2023%2F06%2F30%2Fself-employed-people-in-the-us-are-more-likely-than-other-workers-to-be-highly-satisfied-with-their-jobs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%20Center%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%205%2C902%20Americans%20conducted%20in%20February%202023.%20Compared%20to%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20self-employed%2C%20the%20Americans%20working%20for%20themselves%20report%20finding%20their%20jobs%20more%20enjoyable%20and%20fulfilling%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they're%20not%20as%20stressed.%20Those%20self-employed%20workers%20still%20te